  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency and Transitional Shelter Support for Populations Displaced by Typhoon Ompong, Philippines</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, IOM will provide shelter support to the most vulnerable households in the Cordillera Administrative Region (CAR), with a specific focus on Benguet, and families seeking to return to damaged houses across Cagayan Valley after the typhoon Ompong in the Philippines. Interventions in the targeted areas will focus on the municipality of Itogon, where about 400 households from barangays Ucab and Loacan remain displaced.  To ensure that the most appropriate shelter solution is provided to the wider affected populations across CAR and Cagayan Valley this intervention will make available 4 differentshelter packages adapted to address the most urgent shelter needs identified: Transitional Shelter, Shelter Repair Kits, Emergency ShelterKits, and Cash Grants for those with staying with host families.</narrative>
  </description>
